fno: Turnover on the National Stock Exchange's futures & options (F&O) segment was Rs 105.82 lakh crore compared with Rs 401.20 lakh crore reported in the previous session. In the cash market, the Nifty 50 fell 287.60 points or 1.61% to end at 17,604.35. The NSE's India VIX, a gauge of market's expectation of volatility over the near term, zoomed 18.18% to 17.32. Adani Enterprises, Adani Ports and Special Economic Zone and Ambuja Cement were the top traded individual stock futures contracts in F&O segment of NSE. The February 2023 F&O contracts will expire on 23 February 2023.
